metadata.title: AppKit Release Notes for macOS Ventura 13

inlineContent.text: AppKit in macOS Ventura 13 includes new features, as well as API changes and deprecations.
Color wells have a modernized appearance and two new styles in macOS 13. See the new
property and associated
type for more information on configuring a color well’s style.
The two new color well styles,
and
, offer a pull-down capability. By default, interacting with the well displays a popover with a palette of color choices for quick picking. Applications can customize this interaction using the new
and
properties.
Borderless color wells will be deprecated in a future release. The
property has been annotated as such.
macOS 13 introduces a new type of control:
. NSComboButton provides the functionality of a pull-down menu along with a primary action.
NSComboButton is configurable with two styles,
and
. Refer to the class documentation for guidance on the appearance and behavior of each case.
The
doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsnib/1547299-initwithcontentsofurl
initializer (deprecated since 10.8) now throws an assertion. Use
instead.
On macOS 13 and higher, changing the
property from one value to another will automatically persist autosave data for the old value before changing to the new value. Setting
to
removes the persistence data for the previously set
NSTableView and NSOutlineView now automatically estimate row heights for view-based table views whose delegates implement
and provide variable row heights. This provides performance improvements for table views with large numbers of rows by reducing the frequency of the calls to
To get the benefit of row height estimation, the table view must be view-based and not override
, or
For cell-based table views, checking Autosave Column Information in Interface Builder now correctly persists column information for columns that have automatic column identifiers.
For apps linked against the macOS 13 SDK,
and subclasses that override
now draw their separators correctly, even when displayed as floating group rows.

Placing an NSToolbarItem item taller than the toolbar height is not supported and will result in clipping. When drawing a custom badge, use alignmentRectInsets of the control to describe where the button is and draw within the inset area.

abstract.text: Constants that specify the appearance and interaction modes for a color well.
A style that supports a color picker popover for fast interactions, and adds a dedicated button to display the color panel.
A style that adds minimal adornments to the color well.
The appearance and interaction style to apply to the color well.
A Boolean value that determines whether the color well has a border.
The action to perform when someone clicks in the color area of the color well.
The target object that defines the action you want to perform when someone interacts with the color well.
A button with a pull-down menu and a default action.
A style that separates the button’s title and image from the menu indicator people use to activate the button.
A style that unifies the button’s title and image with the menu indicator.
Returns an `NSNib` object initialized to the nib file in the specified bundle.
The view shown for a row in a table view.
Draws the horizontal separator between table rows.
The name under which table information is automatically saved.
Returns the rectangle containing the row at the specified index.
Returns the index of the row the specified point lies in.
Returns a range of indexes for the rows that lie wholly or partially within the vertical boundaries of the specified rectangle.
Asks the delegate for the height of the specified row.
